    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="561"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d561fn1">Presumably sent via military channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-09">9 March
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>613. Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                    >Roosevelt</persName>. Personal and secret.…<note n="2" xml:id="d561fn2">For the
                        full text of this telegram, see <persName corresp="#p_CC2"
                            >Churchill</persName>, <ref target="#pg_697">p. 697</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>You will remember that we discussed the dollar balances in Cairo on
                        December 8th and that I gave a memorandum to <persName corresp="#p_HHL1"
                            >Harry</persName>.<note n="3" xml:id="d561fn3">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> left Cairo on the
                            morning of December 7, 1943. For what is believed to be the memorandum
                            given to <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Harry Hopkins</persName>, see <hi
                                rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_822">p. 822</ref>.</note>
                        <pb facs="0983" n="879" xml:id="pg_879"/> I certainly understood that you
                        felt we ought not to be treated worse than France or Russia in these
                        matters.…</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
